China’s Youku Jumps Most in 6 Months on Warner Bros. Partnership

-- B y   B e l i n d a   C a o
-- 
2011-06-28T18:06:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/china-s-youku-jumps-most-in-6-months-on-warner-bros-partnership.html
Youku.com Inc. (YOKU) , China’s largest
online video site, jumped the most in six months in New York
trading after partnering with  Warner Bros . to offer U.S. video-
on-demand titles to Chinese Internet users.  The company’s American depositary receipts soared 31
percent to $35.93 at 2:02 p.m. New York time. It earlier surged
33 percent, the biggest intraday gain since December.  Youku signed a digital distribution agreement with CAV
Warner Home Entertainment Co Ltd. in China, it said in a
statement today. Youku will add a total 400 to 450 Warner Bros.
films to its content library under the three-year contract, it
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Belinda Cao in New York at 
